    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Most of the people already gave the answer but this one is just for making someone's life easier.</p>\n<p>TL;DR</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4e70h.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4e70h.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add test sources\" /></a></p>\n<p>You must add the test folder as source.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Right click on java directory under test</li>\n<li>Mark it as Tests</li>\n<li>Add src/test/java in Test Source Folders</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Thats it, IntelliJ will consider them as test source.</p>\n"
